    "contents" : "---\ntitle: \"Graded Novelty Encoding Task - 3D - analysis\"\noutput:\n  html_document:\n    toc: true\n    toc_float: \n      collapsed: false\n    toc_depth: 4\n---\nThe paradigm\n\n-Familiarization phase\nParticipants see 5 stimuli repeated 8 times each. Stimuli consist of a 3x3 grid, with 5 random shapes (circle,triangle,square) placed randomly (any 9 cells) with random color (red,blue,yellow,green,orange,purple).\n\n-Study phase\nParticipants see the 5 familiar stimuli 5 times each (25) and 50 novel stimuli. They have to judge if the current stimulus is one of the familiars. The novels differ to a differing degree from the familiars: there is 5x2 (two for each familiar) that is wholly different (diffarr). 5x2 that has the same placement of random shapes (sarr), 5x2 same arrangement and shapes (sarrsha), 5x2 same arrangement and colors (sarrcol) 5x2 same arrangement, shapes and colors (colors are randomized, thus, these are not the same as the familiars - sarrshacol). \n\n-Test phase\nParticipants see the novels from the study phase and 50 new stimuli (sarr - 10, sarrsha - 10, etc.). Participants have to signal if they have already seen the current stimulus or it is wholly new. They had the option to signal \"maybe\", but were asked to do this in moderation (maybe resp <= 20). These responses have been added to correct responses.\n\n```{r  include=FALSE}\nlibrary(ez)\nlibrary(ggplot2)\nlibrary(emmeans)\nlibrary(DescTools)\nlibrary(stats)\nlibrary(afex)\nlibrary(effsize)\nlibrary(lubridate)\nlibrary(Hmisc)\nsource(\"difference_innumbers.R\")\nsource(\"datproc_3d.R\")\nGNET_pilot_alldata <- GNET_3d_alldata\nrm(GNET_3d_alldata)\n\n# EXCLUSIONs ####\n\n# extract the number of all separate runs - allruns\nallruns <- unique(GNET_pilot_alldata[,c(\"studyResultId\",\"workerId\")])\nallruns <- na.omit(allruns)\nallruns <- nrow(allruns)\n\n# REMOVE INSUFFICIENT DATA\nids <- GNET_pilot_alldata[, .(rowCount = .N), by = c(\"workerId\",\"studyResultId\",\"datetime\")]\nids[,RUNIDENTIFIER := paste(ids$workerId, \"_\", ids$studyResultId, sep=\"\")]\nids <- ids[rowCount >= 175]\nGNET_pilot_alldata <-\n  GNET_pilot_alldata[workerId %in% ids$workerId & studyResultId %in% ids$studyResultId,]\nGNET_pilot_alldata <- \n  GNET_pilot_alldata[!duplicated(GNET_pilot_alldata),]\ncompleteruns <- nrow(ids)\n\n# REMOVE TOO MUCH MISSED RESPONSES\nResponsesSummary <- GNET_pilot_alldata[, .(rowCount = .N), by = .(workerId,studyResultId,type,tq,response)]\nMissedResSummary <- ResponsesSummary[response == \"None\", sum(rowCount),by = .(workerId,studyResultId)]\nMissedResSummary <- MissedResSummary[V1 < 66,]\nGNET_pilot_alldata <-\n  GNET_pilot_alldata[(workerId %in% MissedResSummary$workerId) & (studyResultId %in% MissedResSummary$studyResultId),]\n# Nr of exclusions due to misses\nExcludeMisses <- nrow(ids) - nrow(MissedResSummary)\n\n# túl alacsony prototype recog rate a study alatt kipottyan\nStudySummary <- GNET_pilot_alldata[is.na(count_test_sequence) & response == \"left\" & type == \"prototype\", .N/25, by=.(workerId,studyResultId)]\nStudyFA <- GNET_pilot_alldata[is.na(count_test_sequence) & response == \"left\" & type != \"prototype\", .N/50, by=.(workerId,studyResultId)]\nStudyCR <- merge(StudySummary, StudyFA,by=c(\"workerId\",\"studyResultId\"), all = TRUE)\ncolnames(StudyCR) <- c(\"workerId\",\"studyResultId\",\"R\",\"FA\")\nStudyCR[is.na(FA), FA:=0]\nStudyCR[,CR := R - FA]\n\nStudyBinom <- GNET_pilot_alldata[is.na(count_test_sequence) & response == \"left\",.(workerId,studyResultId,response,type),]\nStudyBinom$RespBinomial <- 0\nStudyBinom[type == \"prototype\", RespBinomial := 1]\nhandles <- unique(StudyBinom[,.(workerId,studyResultId)])\nStudyCR$CI_lower <- 0\nStudyCR$CI_upper <- 0\nfor (i in 1:nrow(handles)){\n  tempBinData <- StudyBinom[workerId == handles$workerId[i] & studyResultId == handles$studyResultId[i],RespBinomial]\n  confint <- binconf(x=sum(tempBinData), n=length(tempBinData))\n  StudyCR[workerId == handles$workerId[i] & studyResultId == handles$studyResultId[i], CI_lower := confint[2]]\n  StudyCR[workerId == handles$workerId[i] & studyResultId == handles$studyResultId[i], CI_upper := confint[3]]\n}\n\n# exclusion crit based on corrected recog rate\nStudySummary <- StudyCR[CR > 0] # 0.3 is the 20th percentile\n# exclusion crit based on uncorrected recog rate\n# StudySummary <- StudySummary[V1 > 0.5]\nStudySummary <- StudyCR[CI_lower > 0.33]\nExcludePrototypeRecog <- nrow(MissedResSummary) - nrow(StudySummary)\nGNET_pilot_alldata <- GNET_pilot_alldata[(workerId %in% StudySummary$workerId) & (studyResultId %in% MissedResSummary$studyResultId),]\n\n# túl sok maybe response kipottyan\nTestSummary <- GNET_pilot_alldata[!is.na(count_test_sequence) & response == \"down\", .N, by=.(workerId,studyResultId)]\nTestSummary <- TestSummary[N < 25]\nExcludeMaybeResp <- nrow(StudySummary) - nrow(TestSummary)\nGNET_pilot_alldata <-\n  GNET_pilot_alldata[(workerId %in% TestSummary$workerId) & (studyResultId %in% MissedResSummary$studyResultId),]\n\nGNET_pilot_filtered <- GNET_pilot_alldata\n\nrm(GNET_pilot_alldata,ids,MissedResSummary,ResponsesSummary,StudySummary)\n#### exclude those cases where a participant completed multiple runs (only first is kept)\nmultipleruns <- GNET_pilot_filtered[,sum(DTF),by=.(workerId,studyResultId,datetime)]\nmultipleruns$datetime <- mdy_hms(multipleruns$datetime)\nmrs <- c(multipleruns$workerId[duplicated(multipleruns$workerId)])\nfor (i in 1:length(mrs)){\n  temp <- multipleruns[workerId == mrs[i]]\n  first <- min(temp$datetime)\n  temp <- temp[datetime != first,]\n  GNET_pilot_filtered <- GNET_pilot_filtered[!(workerId %in% temp & studyResultId %in% temp),]\n}\nrm(temp,first,multipleruns)\nExcludeMRuns <- length(mrs)\nrm(mrs)\n#####\n```\n\n\n# Participants\n\nThe online task has been started a total of `r allruns` times.\n\nWe excluded a total of `r allruns - completeruns` runs due to irregular data leaving `r completeruns` in the analysis.\n\nWe excluded some (`r ExcludeMisses`) runs as they missed more than 66 of 175 trials.\n\nWe also excluded `r ExcludePrototypeRecog` runs in which the participant produced less than 0.3 corrected recognition rate for familiars in the study phase.\n\nWe also excluded `r ExcludeMaybeResp` participants as they overused \"maybe\" responses in the test phase (more than 25).\n\nWe also excluded `r ExcludeMRuns` run(s) as only the first run is kept in the analysis from one participant.\n\nThis left a total of `r nrow(GNET_pilot_filtered)/175` participants.\n\nMaybe responses [mean(±sd)] : `r mean(TestSummary$N)` ± `r sd(TestSummary$N)`\n\n```{r  include=FALSE}\nsource(\"registerdata_in_3d.R\")\n\njkwid <- jkwid[workerId %in% TestSummary$workerId,]\njkwid$gen <- as.character(jkwid$gen)\njkwid[gen == \"Nő\", gen := 1]\njkwid[gen == \"Férfi\", gen := 0]\njkwid$gen <- as.numeric(jkwid$gen)\n```\n\nThe sample had a mean(±sd) age of `r mean(jkwid$age)` ± `r sd(jkwid$age)`.\n\nThe sample contained `r sum(jkwid$gen)` women.\n\n```{r  include=FALSE}\nsource(\"means_1strun.R\")\nStudy_CorrRejectionByType_1R <- Study_CorrRejectionByType\nStudy_ResponsesByType_1R <- Study_ResponsesByType\nTest_ResponsesByType_1R <- Test_ResponsesByType\nrm(Study_CorrRejectionByType,Study_ResponsesByType,Test_ResponsesByType)\nsource(\"means_2ndrun.R\")\nStudy_CorrRejectionByType_2R <- Study_CorrRejectionByType\nStudy_ResponsesByType_2R <- Study_ResponsesByType\nTest_ResponsesByType_2R <- Test_ResponsesByType\nrm(Study_CorrRejectionByType,Study_ResponsesByType,Test_ResponsesByType)\n# unite the data from the two runs\nStudy_CorrRejectionByType <- rbind(Study_CorrRejectionByType_1R,Study_CorrRejectionByType_2R)\nStudy_ResponsesByType <- rbind(Study_ResponsesByType_1R,Study_ResponsesByType_2R)\nTest_ResponsesByType <- rbind(Test_ResponsesByType_1R,Test_ResponsesByType_2R)\nrm(Study_CorrRejectionByType_1R,Study_CorrRejectionByType_2R,\n   Study_ResponsesByType_1R,Study_ResponsesByType_2R,\n   Test_ResponsesByType_1R,Test_ResponsesByType_2R)\n```\n\n```{r  eval = TRUE, warning=FALSE, echo=FALSE}\nlibrary(corrplot)\nlibrary(forcats)\nx <- cor(difference_indices[,c(3:6,8)])\ncorrplot(x, type=\"upper\", method = \"number\", sig.level = 0.0000001, insig = \"blank\")\n\nd <- melt(difference_indices, id.vars=c(\"pict\",\"type\"))\nd <- d[variable %in% c(\"DTF\",\"DTAF\",\"DTN\"),]\n\nd$pict <- fct_reorder(d$pict, d$type)\nnames <- c(`DTF` = \"DTF\",`DTAF` = \"DTAF\",`DTN` = \"DTAN\")\nggplot(d, aes(x = pict, y = as.numeric(value), color = type)) +\n  geom_point() +\n  facet_grid(variable ~ ., labeller = as_labeller(names)) +\n  theme(\n  axis.text.x = element_blank(),\n  axis.ticks.x = element_blank()) +\n  xlab(\"Stimuli\") + \n  ylab(\"Difference score\") +\n  scale_color_discrete(name = \"Stimulus category\", labels=c(\"diffarr\" = \"fully novel\", \"sarr\" = \"novel shapes & colors\", \"sarrcol\" = \"novel shapes\", \"sarrsha\" = \"novel colors\", \"sarrshacol\" = \"novel color combinations\")) \n```\n\n# Study phase:\n\nDuring the study phase, the participants see familiar and novel items.\n\nThe participants produced a mean (±sd) recognition rate of `r mean(Study_ResponsesByType$N[Study_ResponsesByType$type == \"prototype\" & Study_ResponsesByType$response == \"left\"])/25` ± `r sd(Study_ResponsesByType$N[Study_ResponsesByType$type == \"prototype\" & Study_ResponsesByType$response == \"left\"])/25` for familiar pictures.\n\n```{r  eval = TRUE, warning=FALSE, echo=FALSE}\ntest <- t.test(Study_ResponsesByType$N[Study_ResponsesByType$type == \"prototype\" & Study_ResponsesByType$response == \"left\"]/25,\n               mu = 0.5,\n               alternative = \"two.sided\")\ncohend <- cohen.d(Study_ResponsesByType$N[Study_ResponsesByType$type == \"prototype\" & Study_ResponsesByType$response == \"left\"]/25,NA,\n                  paired = FALSE,conf.level=0.95, mu = 0.5)\n\nfams <- Study_ResponsesByType$N[Study_ResponsesByType$type == \"prototype\" & Study_ResponsesByType$response == \"left\"]/25\nnovels <- Study_ResponsesByType[type != \"prototype\" & response == \"left\",sum(N),by=workerId]\nnovels <- novels$V1/50\ncorrectedfamrec <- fams - novels\n\ntest2 <- t.test(correctedfamrec,\n               mu = 0.0,\n               alternative = \"two.sided\")\ncohend2 <- cohen.d(correctedfamrec,NA,\n                  paired = FALSE,conf.level=0.95, mu = 0.0)\n\n```\n\nThe participants produced a mean (±sd) corrected recognition rate of `r mean(fams - novels)` ± `r sd(fams - novels)` for familiar pictures.\n\nUncorrected: The sample performed above chance levels, as a one sample t-test showed (t(`r test$parameter[[1]]`)=`r test$statistic[[1]]`, p = `r test$p.value`, Cohen's d = `r cohend$estimate`, 95% CI:`r cohend$conf.int[[1]]` - `r cohend$conf.int[[2]]`).\n\nCorrected: The sample performed above chance levels, as a one sample t-test showed (t(`r test2$parameter[[1]]`)=`r test2$statistic[[1]]`, p = `r test2$p.value`, Cohen's d = `r cohend2$estimate`, 95% CI:`r cohend2$conf.int[[1]]` - `r cohend2$conf.int[[2]]`).\n\nWe use an ANOVA to see if there is a difference in correct rejection for the different novels.\n```{r  eval = TRUE, warning=FALSE, echo=FALSE}\n# ezANOVA(study_dat_news, dv =  crrate, within = type, wid = workerId)\na1 <- aov_ez(\"workerId\", \"N\",\n             Study_CorrRejectionByType, within = \"type\")\na1\nm3 <- emmeans(a1, ~ type)\npairs(m3)\ncontrast(m3, \"poly\")\nggplot(Study_CorrRejectionByType, aes(x=type, y=N, color = type)) + \n  geom_jitter(width=0.2, alpha=0.2) +\n  stat_summary(geom = \"errorbar\", fun.data = mean_se, width = 0.2) +\n  stat_summary(geom = \"point\",fun.y = \"mean\",col = \"black\",size = 2,shape = 16) +\n  stat_summary(fun.y=mean, colour=\"black\", geom=\"text\", show.legend = FALSE, \n               vjust=-3.0, aes( label=round(..y.., digits=3))) +\n  scale_x_discrete(labels=c(\"diffarr\" = \"fully novel\", \"sarr\" = \"novel shapes & colors\",\n                              \"sarrcol\" = \"novel shapes\", \"sarrsha\" = \"novel colors\", \"sarrshacol\" = \"novel color combinations\")) + \n  ggtitle(\"Number of correct rejections in the study phase by novel picture category\") +\n  xlab(\"\") +\n  ylab(\"Nr of correct rejections\") +\n  theme(legend.position = \"none\")\n```\n\n# Test phase:\n\nThis phase tests the learning that has occurred during the study phase. If the participants learned the novels in the study phase, their responses should differ for the stimuli that they have already seen during the study phase (familiars) and those that they see for the first time during the test phase (novels). We also let the participants to choose \"maybe\" by pressing the down arrow, but asked them not to overuse this response (maybe resp <= 50). We added these responses as correct responses to both stimulus categories.\n\n```{r  warning=FALSE, echo=FALSE}\nmayberesps <- GNET_pilot_filtered[!(is.na(count_test_sequence)) & response == \"down\",.(rowCount = .N),by=c(\"workerId\",\"studyResultId\")]\n```\n\nMaybe responses (MEAN ± SD): `r mean(mayberesps$rowCount)` ± `r sd(mayberesps$rowCount)`.\n\n```{r  warning=FALSE, echo=FALSE}\nlibrary(rstatix)\n\nprint(\"A t-test to compare the number of old responses btwn old and new stim\")\n# print(t.test(test_dat_c_tq$V1[test_dat_c_tq$rkey == \"left\" & test_dat_c_tq$tq == \"fam\"],test_dat_c_tq$V1[test_dat_c_tq$rkey == \"left\" & test_dat_c_tq$tq == \"new\"], paired=TRUE))\n\na <- Test_ResponsesByType$recog_O\nb <- Test_ResponsesByType$fa_N\nttest2 <- t.test(a,b,paired = TRUE)\ncd2 <- cohen.d(a,b,paired = TRUE,conf.level=0.95)\nd <- with(Test_ResponsesByType, recog_O - fa_N)\nst2 <- shapiro.test(d)\n\nwtest <- wilcox.test(a,b,paired = TRUE,conf.level = 0.95)\nrec <- Test_ResponsesByType[,c(\"workerId\",\"recog_O\")]\nrec$type <- \"old\"\ncolnames(rec) <- c(\"workerId\",\"resp\",\"type\")\nfa <- Test_ResponsesByType[,c(\"workerId\",\"fa_N\")]\nfa$type <- \"new\"\ncolnames(fa) <- c(\"workerId\",\"resp\",\"type\")\nweffdat <- rbind(rec,fa)\nweff <- wilcox_effsize(weffdat,resp ~ type, mu = 0, paired=FALSE)\nrm(rec,fa,weffdat)\n\ndlong <- melt(Test_ResponsesByType[,c(\"workerId\", \"type\", \"recog_O\", \"fa_N\")], id.vars=c(\"workerId\", \"type\"))  \n\n#\"value\" and \"variable\" are default output column names of melt()\nggplot(dlong, aes(variable,value, color=type)) +\n  stat_summary(geom = \"point\",fun.y = \"mean\",size = 2,shape = 16,position=position_dodge(width=0.4)) +\n  stat_summary(geom = \"errorbar\", fun.data = \"mean_se\", width = 0.2,position=position_dodge(width=0.4)) +\n  stat_summary(fun.y=mean, geom=\"text\", show.legend = FALSE, \n               vjust=0.0,hjust=1.5, position=position_dodge(width=0.4),aes( label=round(..y.., digits=3))) +\n  #geom_jitter(width=0.2, alpha=0.2) +\n  stat_summary(geom = \"errorbar\", fun.data = \"mean_se\", col =\"black\", width = 0.2) +\n  stat_summary(geom = \"point\",fun.y = \"mean\",col=\"black\",size = 2,shape = 16) +\n  stat_summary(fun.y=mean, colour=\"black\", geom=\"text\", show.legend = FALSE, \n               vjust=0.0,hjust=-1, aes( label=round(..y.., digits=3))) +\n  scale_color_discrete(name = \"Stimulus category\", labels=c(\"diffarr\" = \"fully novel\", \"sarr\" = \"novel shapes & colors\",\"sarrcol\" = \"novel shapes\", \"sarrsha\" = \"novel colors\", \"sarrshacol\" = \"novel color combinations\")) + \n  ylab(\"Mean 'already seen' responses\") + \n  xlab(\"\") + \n  scale_x_discrete(labels=c(\"recog_O\" = \"Correct recognition\", \"fa_N\" = \"False positive\"))\nrm(dlong)\n```\n\nResults of the paired t-test: (t(`r ttest2$parameter[[1]]`)=`r ttest2$statistic[[1]]`, p = `r ttest2$p.value`, Cohen's d = `r cd2$estimate`, 95% CI:`r cd2$conf.int[[1]]` - `r cd2$conf.int[[2]]`).\n\nShapiro-Wilk is significant (p = `r st2$p.value`).\n\nWe used a Wilcoxon sgined-rank test. Z = `r qnorm(wtest$p.value)`, p = `r wtest$p.value`\n\n## ANOVA - Corrected Recog\n\n```{r  warning=FALSE, echo=FALSE}\n\nTest_ResponsesByType$neworder <- \"\"\nTest_ResponsesByType[type == \"diffarr\", neworder := \"A\"]\nTest_ResponsesByType[type == \"sarr\", neworder := \"B\"]\nTest_ResponsesByType[type == \"sarrcol\", neworder := \"D\"]\nTest_ResponsesByType[type == \"sarrsha\", neworder := \"C\"]\nTest_ResponsesByType[type == \"sarrshacol\", neworder := \"E\"]\n\nsetorder(Test_ResponsesByType, neworder)\n\na1 <- aov_ez(\"workerId\", \"CorrRecog\",\n             Test_ResponsesByType, within = c(\"neworder\"))\na1\nm3 <- emmeans(a1, ~ neworder)\npairs(m3)\nposthoc <- pairs(m3)\ncontrast(m3, \"poly\")\n\nggplot(Test_ResponsesByType, aes(x=neworder, y=CorrRecog, color=neworder))+\n  geom_jitter(width=0.3, alpha=0.3) +\n  stat_summary(geom = \"errorbar\", fun.data = mean_se, col = \"black\", width = 0.2) +\n  stat_summary(geom = \"point\",fun.y = \"mean\",col = \"black\",size = 2,shape = 16) +\n  stat_summary(fun.y=mean, colour=\"black\", geom=\"text\", show.legend = FALSE, \n               vjust=-3.0, aes( label=round(..y.., digits=3))) +\n  scale_x_discrete(labels=c(\"A\" = \"fully novel\", \"B\" = \"novel shapes & colors\",\n                              \"D\" = \"novel shapes\", \"C\" = \"novel colors\", \"E\" = \"novel color combinations\")) +\n  ggtitle(\"Corrected recognition score in the test phase by picture category\")+\n  xlab(\"\")+\n  ylab(\"\")+\n  theme(legend.position = \"none\")\n\nndf <- a1$anova_table$`num Df`\nddf <- a1$anova_table$`den Df`\np <- a1$anova_table$`Pr(>F)`\n```\n\nANOVA (factor: TYPE (5 lvls)): (F[`r ndf`,`r ddf`] = `r a1$anova_table$F`, p = `r p`, n2G = `r a1$anova_table$ges`).\n\n## ANOVA - Corrected Rejec\n\n```{r  warning=FALSE, echo=FALSE}\na1 <- aov_ez(\"workerId\", \"CorrRejec\",\n             Test_ResponsesByType, within = c(\"neworder\"))\na1\nm3 <- emmeans(a1, ~ neworder)\npairs(m3)\nposthoc <- pairs(m3)\ncontrast(m3, \"poly\")\n\nggplot(Test_ResponsesByType, aes(x=neworder, y=CorrRejec, color=neworder))+\n  geom_jitter(width=0.3, alpha=0.3) +\n  stat_summary(geom = \"errorbar\", fun.data = mean_se, col = \"black\", width = 0.2) +\n  stat_summary(geom = \"point\",fun.y = \"mean\",col = \"black\",size = 2,shape = 16) +\n  stat_summary(fun.y=mean, colour=\"black\", geom=\"text\", show.legend = FALSE, \n               vjust=-3.0, aes( label=round(..y.., digits=3))) +\n  scale_x_discrete(labels=c(\"A\" = \"fully novel\", \"B\" = \"novel shapes & colors\",\n                              \"D\" = \"novel shapes\", \"C\" = \"novel colors\", \"E\" = \"novel color combinations\")) +\n  ggtitle(\"Corrected rejection score in the test phase by picture category\")+\n  xlab(\"\")+\n  ylab(\"\")+\n  theme(legend.position = \"none\")\n\nndf <- a1$anova_table$`num Df`\nddf <- a1$anova_table$`den Df`\np <- a1$anova_table$`Pr(>F)`\n```\n\nANOVA (factor: TYPE (5 levels)): (F[`r ndf`,`r ddf`] = `r a1$anova_table$F`, p = `r p`, n2G = `r a1$anova_table$ges`).\n\n## ANOVA - Overall Performance Score\n\n```{r  warning=FALSE, echo=FALSE}\na1 <- aov_ez(\"workerId\", \"OverallCCat\",\n             Test_ResponsesByType, within = c(\"neworder\"))\na1\nm3 <- emmeans(a1, ~ neworder)\npairs(m3)\nposthoc <- pairs(m3)\ncontrast(m3, \"poly\")\n\nggplot(Test_ResponsesByType, aes(x=neworder, y=OverallCCat, color=neworder))+\n  geom_jitter(width=0.3, alpha=0.3) +\n  stat_summary(geom = \"errorbar\", fun.data = mean_se, col = \"black\", width = 0.2) +\n  stat_summary(geom = \"point\",fun.y = \"mean\",col = \"black\",size = 2,shape = 16) +\n  stat_summary(fun.y=mean, colour=\"black\", geom=\"text\", show.legend = FALSE, \n               vjust=-3.0, aes( label=round(..y.., digits=3))) +\n  scale_x_discrete(labels=c(\"A\" = \"fully novel\", \"B\" = \"novel shapes & colors\",\n                              \"D\" = \"novel shapes\", \"C\" = \"novel colors\", \"E\" = \"novel color combinations\")) +\n  ggtitle(\"Overall corrected categorization score in the test phase by picture category\")+\n  xlab(\"\")+\n  ylab(\"\")+\n  theme(legend.position = \"none\")\n\nndf <- a1$anova_table$`num Df`\nddf <- a1$anova_table$`den Df`\np <- a1$anova_table$`Pr(>F)`\n```\n\nANOVA (factor: TYPE (5 levels)): (F[`r ndf`,`r ddf`] = `r a1$anova_table$F`, p = `r p`, n2G = `r a1$anova_table$ges`).\n\n## - ANOVA - Orig vs 3D\n\n```{r  warning=FALSE, echo=FALSE}\nOrig_Test_ResponsesByType <- read.csv(\"gnet-orig_testrespsummary.csv\")\nOrig_Test_ResponsesByType <- Orig_Test_ResponsesByType[,c(\"workerId\",\"type\",\"CorrRecog\",\"CorrRejec\",\"OverallCCat\",\"neworder\")]\nOrig_Test_ResponsesByType$Version <- \"Original\"\n\n\nNu3D_Test_ResponsesByType <- Test_ResponsesByType[,c(\"workerId\",\"type\",\"CorrRecog\",\"CorrRejec\",\"OverallCCat\",\"neworder\")]\nNu3D_Test_ResponsesByType$Version <- \"3D\"\n\nOrig_and_3D_TestRBT <- rbind(Orig_Test_ResponsesByType,Nu3D_Test_ResponsesByType)\n\na1 <- aov_ez(\"workerId\", \"OverallCCat\",\n             Orig_and_3D_TestRBT, within = c(\"neworder\"), between = c(\"Version\"))\na1\nm3 <- emmeans(a1, ~ Version | neworder)\npairs(m3)\nposthoc <- pairs(m3)\ncontrast(m3, \"poly\")\n\nggplot(Orig_and_3D_TestRBT, aes(x=neworder, y=OverallCCat, color=Version))+\n  geom_jitter(width=0.3, alpha=0.3) +\n  stat_summary(geom = \"errorbar\", fun.data = mean_se, col = \"black\", width = 0.2) +\n  stat_summary(geom = \"point\",fun.y = \"mean\",col = \"black\",size = 2,shape = 16) +\n  stat_summary(fun.y=mean, colour=\"black\", geom=\"text\", show.legend = FALSE, \n               vjust=-3.0, aes( label=round(..y.., digits=3))) +\n  scale_x_discrete(labels=c(\"A\" = \"f. n.\", \"B\" = \"n. sha. & col.\",\n                              \"D\" = \"n. sha.\", \"C\" = \"n. col.\", \"E\" = \"n. col. comb.\")) +\n  ggtitle(\"Overall corrected categorization score in the test phase by picture category\")+\n  xlab(\"\")+\n  ylab(\"\")+\n  theme(legend.position = \"none\") +\n  facet_grid(~Version)\n\nndf <- a1$anova_table$`num Df`\nddf <- a1$anova_table$`den Df`\np <- a1$anova_table$`Pr(>F)`\n```\n\n# Mixed models\n\nThe metrics\n\n-DTF - Difference To corresponding Familiar picture\nAll pictures are compared to a familiar. The number of differences between the three vectors of the pictures yields a difference score.\n\n-DTAF - mean Difference To All Familiars\nWe calculate the difference from all prototypes and take the mean for each picture in the set.\n\n-DTAN - mean Difference To All other Novels in the same category\nWe calculate the differences between each pair of pictures and then take the mean of these differences (19 comparisons per stim).\n\n-DTN_byPhase - mean Difference to Novels in the same category per study/test phase\nWe calculate the differences between each pair of pictures and then take the mean of these differences (9 comparisons per stim).\n\n-DTPPm - mean Diff To Previously seen Pictures\nWe compare the current picture to all previously seen pictures (25 in first study trial, 26 in 2nd, and so on ..). We take the mean.\n\n-DTN - Difference to all novels - compare a stimulus to all novels and take the mean.\n\n```{r  include=FALSE}\nlibrary(lme4)\nlibrary(lmerTest)\nlibrary(sjPlot)\n\n# we use a preprocessed DT which holds the data of the 59 participants that were not thrown out\nlmmdat <- GNET_pilot_filtered\n\n# lmmdat$DTF <- scale(lmmdat$DTF)\n# lmmdat$DTAF <- scale(lmmdat$DTAF)\n# lmmdat$DTAN <- scale(lmmdat$DTAN)\n# lmmdat$DTN_byPhase <- scale(lmmdat$DTN_byPhase)\n# lmmdat$DTN <- scale(lmmdat$DTN)\n\nstlmm <- lmmdat[is.na(count_test_sequence),]\nstlmm$st_corr <- 0\nstlmm[type == \"prototype\" & response == \"left\", st_corr := 1]\nstlmm[type != \"prototype\" & response == \"right\", st_corr := 1]\n\ntdlmm <- lmmdat[!(is.na(count_test_sequence)),]\n\ntdlmm$rt_resp <- 0\ntdlmm[response == \"left\",rt_resp := 1]\ntdlmm[response == \"right\",rt_resp := 0]\ntdlmm[response == \"down\",rt_resp := NA]\ntdlmm[response == \"None\",rt_resp := NA]\n\nt2lmm <- merge(stlmm,tdlmm,by=c(\"datetime\",\"stim\",\n                  \"workerId\",\"type\",\"DTF\",\"DTAF\",\"DTAN\",\"DTN_byPhase\",\"DTN\"))\n```\n\n## Study phase\n\nWith these models i tried to assess which difference index explains familiar v novel distinction in study phase the best. As far as i understand, the model with the smallest AIC fits best to our data, which means that the mean difference from the corresponding familiar worked best here. The models all show, that the more different pictures are categorized with the highest efficacy.\n\n```{r  eval = TRUE, warning=FALSE, echo=FALSE}\n# 1St model\nlogmr <- glmer(st_corr ~ factor(type) + (1|workerId),\n               data = stlmm,\n               family = binomial)\nsummary(logmr)\nplot_model(logmr, type = \"eff\")\n# 2Nd model\nlogmr2 <- glmer(st_corr ~ DTF + (1|workerId),\n               data = stlmm,\n               family = binomial)\nsummary(logmr2)\nplot_model(logmr2, type = \"eff\")\n# 3Rd model\nlogmr3 <- glmer(st_corr ~ DTAF + (1|workerId),\n               data = stlmm,\n               family = binomial)\nsummary(logmr3)\nplot_model(logmr3, type = \"eff\")\n# 4th model\nlogmr4 <- glmer(st_corr ~ DTAN + (1|workerId),\n               data = stlmm,\n               family = binomial)\nsummary(logmr4)\nplot_model(logmr4, type = \"eff\")\n# 5th model\nlogmr5 <- glmer(st_corr ~ DTN_byPhase + (1|workerId),\n               data = stlmm,\n               family = binomial)\nsummary(logmr5)\nplot_model(logmr5, type = \"eff\")\n# 6th model\nlogmr6 <- glmer(st_corr ~ DTN + (1|workerId),\n               data = stlmm,\n               family = binomial)\nsummary(logmr6)\nplot_model(logmr6, type = \"eff\")\n\ntab_model(logmr, logmr2,logmr3,logmr4,logmr5,logmr6,\n          # = c(\"Model 1\", \"Model 2\", \"Model 3\", \"Model 4\"),\n          show.est = TRUE,\n          # show.ci = TRUE,\n          show.se = TRUE,\n          show.r2 = TRUE,\n          # show.adj.icc = TRUE,\n          # show.icc = FALSE,\n          # pred.labels =\n          show.aic = TRUE,\n          show.aicc = TRUE,\n          # show.std = TRUE,\n          transform = NULL)\n```\n\n## Test phase\n\n### Models #1\n\nLogistic mixed regression for the test phase. Does difference from prototypes or familiarity/novelty have an effect on correct categorization in the test phase?\n\nThese models use trial quality (familiar / novel) as a fixed and as a random effect.\n\nrt_resp is recognition test response, 0 stands for 'old' and 1 stands for 'new'.\n\n```{r  eval = TRUE, warning=FALSE, echo=FALSE}\n\nlogmr <- glmer(rt_resp ~ type * tq + (1|workerId),\n               data = tdlmm,\n               family = binomial)\nsummary(logmr)\nplot_model(logmr, type = \"eff\")$type\nplot_model(logmr, type = \"eff\")$tq\nplot_model(logmr, type = \"int\")\n\nlogmr2 <- glmer(rt_resp ~ DTF * tq + (1|workerId),\n               data = tdlmm,\n               family = binomial)\nsummary(logmr2)\nplot_model(logmr2, type = \"eff\")$DTF\nplot_model(logmr2, type = \"eff\")$tq\nplot_model(logmr2, type = \"int\")\n\nlogmr3 <- glmer(rt_resp ~ DTAF * tq + (1|workerId),\n               data = tdlmm,\n               family = binomial)\nsummary(logmr3)\nplot_model(logmr3, type = \"eff\")$DTAF\nplot_model(logmr3, type = \"eff\")$tq\nplot_model(logmr3, type = \"int\")\n\nlogmr4 <- glmer(rt_resp ~ DTAN * tq + (1|workerId),\n               data = tdlmm,\n               family = binomial)\nsummary(logmr4)\nplot_model(logmr4, type = \"eff\")$DTAN\nplot_model(logmr4, type = \"eff\")$tq\nplot_model(logmr4, type = \"int\")\n\nlogmr5 <- glmer(rt_resp ~ DTN_byPhase * tq + (1|workerId),\n               data = tdlmm,\n               family = binomial)\nsummary(logmr5)\nplot_model(logmr5, type = \"eff\")$DTN_byPhase\nplot_model(logmr5, type = \"eff\")$tq\nplot_model(logmr5, type = \"int\")\n\nlogmr6 <- glmer(rt_resp ~ DTN * tq + (1|workerId),\n              data = tdlmm,\n               family = binomial)\nsummary(logmr6)\nplot_model(logmr6, type = \"eff\")$DTN\nplot_model(logmr6, type = \"eff\")$tq\nplot_model(logmr6, type = \"int\")\n\ntab_model(logmr, logmr2,logmr3,logmr4,logmr5,logmr6,\n          # = c(\"Model 1\", \"Model 2\", \"Model 3\", \"Model 4\"),\n          show.est = TRUE,\n          # show.ci = TRUE,\n          show.se = TRUE,\n          show.r2 = TRUE,\n          # show.adj.icc = TRUE,\n          # show.icc = FALSE,\n          # pred.labels =\n          show.aic = TRUE,\n          show.aicc = TRUE,\n          # show.std = TRUE,\n          transform = NULL)\n\n```\n\n### Models #2\n\nLogistic mixed regression for the test phase. Does difference from prototypes or familiarity/novelty have an effect on correct categorization in the test phase?\n\nThese models use trial quality (familiar / novel) as a fixed effect only.\n\nrt_resp is recognition test response, 0 stands for 'old' and 1 stands for 'new'.\n\n```{r  eval = TRUE, warning=FALSE, echo=FALSE}\n\nlogmr <- glmer(rt_resp ~ type * tq + (tq|workerId),\n               data = tdlmm,\n               family = binomial)\nsummary(logmr)\nplot_model(logmr, type = \"eff\")$type\nplot_model(logmr, type = \"eff\")$tq\nplot_model(logmr, type = \"int\")\n\nlogmr2 <- glmer(rt_resp ~ DTF * tq + (tq|workerId),\n               data = tdlmm,\n               family = binomial)\nsummary(logmr2)\nplot_model(logmr2, type = \"eff\")$DTF +\n  scale_y_continuous(limits = c(0, 0.7), \n                     labels = scales::percent_format(accuracy = 1)) +\n  ggtitle(\"Predicted probability of 'already seen' response\") + \n  ylab(\"\")\n\nplot_model(logmr2, type = \"eff\")$tq +\n  scale_y_continuous(limits = c(0.25, 0.45), \n                     labels = scales::percent_format(accuracy = 1)) +\n  ggtitle(\"Predicted probability of 'already seen' response\") + \n  ylab(\"\") + \n  xlab(\"\") +\n  scale_x_discrete(limits=c(\"new\" = \"distractor\", \"old\" = \"previously presented\"))\n\nplot_model(logmr2, type = \"int\") +\n  scale_y_continuous(limits = c(0, 0.7), \n                     labels = scales::percent_format(accuracy = 1)) +\n  ggtitle(\"Predicted probability of 'already seen' response\") + \n  ylab(\"\") +\n  scale_color_discrete(name = \"Trial type\", labels=c(\"new\" = \"distractor\", \"old\" = \"prev. pres\")) \n\nlogmr3 <- glmer(rt_resp ~ DTAF * tq + (tq|workerId),\n               data = tdlmm,\n               family = binomial)\nsummary(logmr3)\nplot_model(logmr3, type = \"eff\")$DTAF\nplot_model(logmr3, type = \"eff\")$tq\nplot_model(logmr3, type = \"int\")\n\nlogmr4 <- glmer(rt_resp ~ DTAN * tq + (tq|workerId),\n               data = tdlmm,\n               family = binomial)\nsummary(logmr4)\nplot_model(logmr4, type = \"eff\")$DTAN\nplot_model(logmr4, type = \"eff\")$tq\nplot_model(logmr4, type = \"int\")\n\nlogmr5 <- glmer(rt_resp ~ DTN_byPhase * tq + (tq|workerId),\n               data = tdlmm,\n               family = binomial)\nsummary(logmr5)\nplot_model(logmr5, type = \"eff\")$DTN_byPhase\nplot_model(logmr5, type = \"eff\")$tq\nplot_model(logmr5, type = \"int\")\n\nlogmr6 <- glmer(rt_resp ~ DTN * tq + (tq|workerId),\n              data = tdlmm,\n              family = binomial)\nsummary(logmr6)\nplot_model(logmr6, type = \"eff\")$DTN\nplot_model(logmr6, type = \"eff\")$tq\nplot_model(logmr6, type = \"int\")\n\ntab_model(logmr, logmr2,logmr3,logmr4,logmr5,logmr6,\n          # = c(\"Model 1\", \"Model 2\", \"Model 3\", \"Model 4\"),\n          show.est = TRUE,\n          # show.ci = TRUE,\n          show.se = TRUE,\n          show.r2 = TRUE,\n          # show.adj.icc = TRUE,\n          # show.icc = FALSE,\n          # pred.labels =\n          show.aic = TRUE,\n          show.aicc = TRUE,\n          # show.std = TRUE,\n          transform = NULL)\n\n```\n\n### Models #3\n\nDoes the corrected recog rate in the study phase have an effect?\n\n```{r  eval = TRUE, warning=FALSE, echo=FALSE}\nfor (i in 1:nrow(StudyCR)){\n  tdlmm[workerId == StudyCR$workerId[i] & studyResultId == StudyCR$studyResultId[i],stCR := StudyCR$CR[i]]\n}\n\n\nlogmr <- glmer(rt_resp ~ type * tq * stCR + (1|workerId),\n               data = tdlmm,\n               family = binomial,control = lmerControl(optCtrl=list(xtol_abs=1e-8, ftol_abs=1e-8, maxeval=100000)))\nsummary(logmr)\nplot_model(logmr, type = \"eff\")\nplot_model(logmr, type = \"int\")\n\nlogmr2 <- glmer(rt_resp ~ DTF * tq * stCR + (1|workerId),\n               data = tdlmm,\n               family = binomial,control = lmerControl(optCtrl=list(xtol_abs=1e-8, ftol_abs=1e-8, maxeval=100000)))\nsummary(logmr2)\nplot_model(logmr2, type = \"eff\")\nplot_model(logmr2, type = \"int\")\n\nlogmr3 <- glmer(rt_resp ~ DTAF * tq * stCR + (1|workerId),\n               data = tdlmm,\n               family = binomial,control = lmerControl(optCtrl=list(xtol_abs=1e-8, ftol_abs=1e-8, maxeval=100000)))\nsummary(logmr3)\nplot_model(logmr3, type = \"eff\")\nplot_model(logmr3, type = \"int\")\n\nlogmr4 <- glmer(rt_resp ~ DTAN * tq * stCR + (1|workerId),\n               data = tdlmm,\n               family = binomial,control = lmerControl(optCtrl=list(xtol_abs=1e-8, ftol_abs=1e-8, maxeval=100000)))\nsummary(logmr4)\nplot_model(logmr4, type = \"eff\")\nplot_model(logmr4, type = \"int\")\n\nlogmr5 <- glmer(rt_resp ~ DTN_byPhase * tq * stCR + (1|workerId),\n               data = tdlmm,\n               family = binomial,control = lmerControl(optCtrl=list(xtol_abs=1e-8, ftol_abs=1e-8, maxeval=100000)))\nsummary(logmr5)\nplot_model(logmr5, type = \"eff\")\nplot_model(logmr5, type = \"int\")\n\nlogmr6 <- glmer(rt_resp ~ DTN * tq * stCR + (1|workerId),\n              data = tdlmm,\n              family = binomial,control = lmerControl(optCtrl=list(xtol_abs=1e-8, ftol_abs=1e-8, maxeval=100000)))\nsummary(logmr6)\nplot_model(logmr6, type = \"eff\")\nplot_model(logmr6, type = \"int\")\n\ntab_model(logmr, logmr2,logmr3,logmr4,logmr5,logmr6,\n          # = c(\"Model 1\", \"Model 2\", \"Model 3\", \"Model 4\"),\n          show.est = TRUE,\n          # show.ci = TRUE,\n          show.se = TRUE,\n          show.r2 = TRUE,\n          # show.adj.icc = TRUE,\n          # show.icc = FALSE,\n          # pred.labels =\n          show.aic = TRUE,\n          show.aicc = TRUE,\n          # show.std = TRUE,\n          transform = NULL)\n\n```\n\n## Test phase and study response\n\n### Models #1\n\nLogistic mixed regression for the test phase. Does difference from prototypes or familiarity/novelty have an effect on correct categorization in the test phase?\n\nThese models use trial quality (familiar / novel) as a fixed and as a random effect.\n\nrt_resp is recognition test response, 0 stands for 'old' and 1 stands for 'new'.\n\n```{r  eval = TRUE, warning=FALSE, echo=FALSE}\n\nlogmr <- glmer(rt_resp ~ type * st_corr + (1|workerId),\n               data = t2lmm,\n               family = binomial)\nsummary(logmr)\nplot_model(logmr, type = \"eff\")$type\nplot_model(logmr, type = \"eff\")$st_corr\nplot_model(logmr, type = \"int\")\n\nlogmr2 <- glmer(rt_resp ~ DTF * st_corr + (1|workerId),\n               data = t2lmm,\n               family = binomial)\nsummary(logmr2)\nplot_model(logmr2, type = \"eff\")$DTF\nplot_model(logmr2, type = \"eff\")$st_corr\nplot_model(logmr2, type = \"int\")\n\nlogmr3 <- glmer(rt_resp ~ DTAF * st_corr + (1|workerId),\n               data = t2lmm,\n               family = binomial)\nsummary(logmr3)\nplot_model(logmr3, type = \"eff\")$DTAF\nplot_model(logmr3, type = \"eff\")$st_corr\nplot_model(logmr3, type = \"int\")\n\nlogmr4 <- glmer(rt_resp ~ DTAN * st_corr + (1|workerId),\n               data = t2lmm,\n               family = binomial)\nsummary(logmr4)\nplot_model(logmr4, type = \"eff\")$DTAN\nplot_model(logmr4, type = \"eff\")$st_corr\nplot_model(logmr4, type = \"int\")\n\nlogmr5 <- glmer(rt_resp ~ DTN_byPhase * st_corr + (1|workerId),\n               data = t2lmm,\n               family = binomial)\nsummary(logmr5)\nplot_model(logmr5, type = \"eff\")$DTN_byPhase\nplot_model(logmr5, type = \"eff\")$st_corr\nplot_model(logmr5, type = \"int\")\n\nlogmr6 <- glmer(rt_resp ~ DTN * st_corr + (1|workerId),\n               data = t2lmm,\n               family = binomial)\nsummary(logmr6)\nplot_model(logmr6, type = \"eff\")$DTN\nplot_model(logmr6, type = \"eff\")$st_corr\nplot_model(logmr6, type = \"int\")\n\ntab_model(logmr, logmr2,logmr3,logmr4,logmr5,logmr6,\n          # = c(\"Model 1\", \"Model 2\", \"Model 3\", \"Model 4\"),\n          show.est = TRUE,\n          # show.ci = TRUE,\n          show.se = TRUE,\n          show.r2 = TRUE,\n          # show.adj.icc = TRUE,\n          # show.icc = FALSE,\n          # pred.labels =\n          show.aic = TRUE,\n          show.aicc = TRUE,\n          # show.std = TRUE,\n          transform = NULL)\n\n```",
